		<category scheme="https://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Publication" /><category scheme="https://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Web Design and Applications" />
		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[The Media Working Group has published a First Public Working Draft of Media Source Extensions™. This specification extends HTMLMediaElement [HTML] to allow JavaScript to generate media streams for playback. Allowing JavaScript to generate streams facilitates a variety of use cases like adaptive streaming and time shifting live streams.]]></summary>

					<content type="html" xml:base="https://www.w3.org/blog/news/archives/9265"><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="https://www.w3.org/media-wg/">Media Working Group</a> has published a First Public Working Draft of <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2021/WD-media-source-2-20210930/">Media Source Extensions<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2122.png" alt="™" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></a>. This specification extends <a href="https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> [<cite><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2021/WD-media-source-2-20210930/#bib-html">HTML</a></cite>] to allow JavaScript to generate media streams for playback. Allowing JavaScript to generate streams facilitates a variety of use cases like adaptive streaming and time shifting live streams.</p>
