		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[As part of working with the WHATWG together on HTML and DOM, W3C selected today to endorse the DOM Review Draft — Published 15 June 2020 as a W3C Recommendation. DOM defines a platform-neutral model for events, aborting activities, and node trees. For more information, see the blog post WHATWG Review Drafts of HTML and [&#8230;]]]></summary>

					<content type="html" xml:base="https://www.w3.org/blog/news/archives/9262"><![CDATA[<p>As part of working with the WHATWG <a href="https://www.w3.org/blog/2019/05/w3c-and-whatwg-to-work-together-to-advance-the-open-web-platform/">together on HTML and DOM</a>, W3C selected today to endorse the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2021/REC-DOM-20210928/">DOM Review Draft — Published 15 June 2020</a> as a W3C Recommendation. DOM defines a platform-neutral model for events, aborting activities, and node trees. For more information, see the blog post <a href="https://www.w3.org/blog/2021/01/whatwg-review-drafts-of-html-and-dom-endorsed-as-w3c-recommendations/">WHATWG Review Drafts of HTML and DOM endorsed as W3C Recommendations</a>.</p>
